International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 23 Jan 2012
From: Mark Lehman <iyr6@cdc.gov> [edited]


[Ref: Brucellosis, human - USA: (MA), unpasteurized milk 20120121.1017730]
----------------------------------------------------------------------
I have a comment regarding the recent post. A few of the moderators mentioned _Brucella melitensis_ as a possible causative agent. It is important to note that _B. melitensis_ is considered a foreign animal disease in the US and unlikely to be the causative agent in this case. _B. abortus_ is most likely.

--
Dr Mark Lehman
Epidemic Intelligence Service Officer
Bacterial Special Pathogens Branch
Division of High-Consequence Pathogens and Pathology
Centers for Disease Control and Prevention
USA
<iyr6@cdc.gov>

[ProMED-mail thanks Dr Lehman for his comments regarding the isolate from Massachusetts. This moderator was not trying to imply that the organism was _B. melitensis_ but rather just that the isolate was, as yet, not speciated. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1vdg.]
